    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is really strange. Why would we hit the `/derp` endpoint on the IDP?\r\n\r\nMy hunch is the idp took the same port as a coderd from a previous test. Then the other test hit the `/derp` port before it was fully closed.\r\n\r\nI added some logs to output the port of the fake IDP: https://github.com/coder/coder/pull/13818\r\n\r\nIf this happens again with the logs, I can search if the port is being used by more than 1 test",
